---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const description =
  'FarseerTech is a small group that helps companies evolve their product and operations into something leaner and genuinely AI-native — and the honest second opinion you get before you commit the budget.';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description={description} crumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'About' }]}>
  <section class="about">
    <p class="eyebrow mono-label">About</p>
    <h1 class="about-title">A second opinion before you commit the budget.</h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>FarseerTech</strong> is a small group — two or three of us, deliberately —
        that helps companies evolve their whole product and operation into something leaner
        and genuinely AI-native. Not "bolt on a chatbot." The harder, more valuable version:
        rethinking how the product is built and how the business runs so it needs fewer moving
        parts, fewer people to keep it alive, and a smaller bill at the end of the quarter.
      </p>
      <p>
        Mostly, people call us for a <strong>second opinion</strong>. You're about to double
        the team, re-platform onto something fashionable, or pour a year into an "AI strategy"
        — and some quiet part of you wants a senior, outside read <em>before</em> you commit the
        budget. That's our specialty: the frank second opinion, the kind that will happily talk
        you <em>out</em> of the expensive thing.
      </p>
      <p>
        The bias underneath all of it is <strong>frugality</strong>. Complexity and headcount
        feel like progress; usually they're just deferred liability with a nicer name — there's
        a <a href="/field-notes/ai-velocity-manufacturing-liabilities">whole field note</a>
        about that. The simplest system that actually works is harder to find. It takes more
        judgment, not less. But it's the one you can still afford, still run, and still reason
        about when it matters most.
      </p>
      <p class="about-list-intro">In practice that looks like:</p>
      <ul class="about-list">
        <li><strong>Lean operations</strong> — fewer services and steps, run by a handful of people who can hold the whole thing in their heads.</li>
        <li><strong>AI where it actually pays</strong> — automation and agents aimed at real cost and toil, not at a demo.</li>
        <li><strong>Second opinions</strong> — a senior, outside read before you commit budget, headcount, or a rebuild.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 class="founders-heading">Founders</h2>
    <div class="founders">
      <article class="founder">
        <h3 class="founder-name">{SITE.owner}</h3>
        <p class="founder-role mono-label">Founder</p>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            I'm a principal engineering manager at <strong>Microsoft</strong>, where I lead a core
            health, monitoring, and incident-detection platform used across critical cloud services
            and chair architecture for a 200-plus-person AIOps organization spanning 20-plus teams.
            Most of my career has lived in the unglamorous middle of hyperscale cloud — the
            reliability, observability, and AIOps systems that are supposed to notice something's
            broken before your customers do.
          </p>
          <p>
            A few things I'm proud of, told as before-and-after — because that's how I think about
            value: outage detection that climbed from catching ~38% of issues to ~72%, and from
            ~15&nbsp;minutes down to ~3.5; deployment-safety gating that screened 185,000-plus rollouts
            and stopped 10,000-plus bad ones before a single customer felt them; ingestion throughput
            up roughly 8×; database costs cut ~85%; tens of thousands of compute cores reclaimed. I
            grew a team from a handful to a dozen-plus with zero regrettable attrition, mentored
            engineers into principal roles, took a customer-facing cloud service-health offering to
            public preview at <strong>Microsoft Build 2025</strong>, and I'm a named inventor on a
            granted U.S. patent (No.&nbsp;12,587,460) for cloud-service health monitoring — with more
            applications filed.
          </p>
          <p>
            What I care about now is the shift from <em>detecting</em> problems to <em>preventing</em>
            them — multi-agent systems that close the loop — and doing it with far fewer parts than
            everyone expects. That's the whole FarseerTech thesis, honestly: I've seen the production
            bill before it arrives, and I'd rather help you avoid it. B.S. in Computer Science,
            University of Texas at Dallas.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <!--
        Co-founder bios go here. FarseerTech is a 2–3 person group; add each real
        co-founder as another <article class="founder"> once Yusuf supplies their
        actual name/role/background. Do NOT invent people or credentials.
      -->
    </div>

    <p class="about-cta">
      If you're staring down a big build, a bigger team, or an AI roadmap and want a frank
      second opinion first — that's exactly the conversation we like to have.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem) clamp(1.4rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); max-width: 50rem; }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--coral); }
  .about-title {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1.6rem;
    font-size: var(--t-2xl);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    max-width: 20ch;
  }
  .about-list-intro { margin-bottom: 0.3rem !important; }
  .about-list { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; }
  .about-list li { line-height: 1.5; }
  .about-list li::marker { color: var(--coral); }

  .founders-heading {
    margin: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.4rem) 0 0;
    padding-top: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: var(--t-xl);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .founders { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.2rem; }
  .founder-name { margin: 0; font-size: var(--t-lg); letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .founder-role { margin: 0.15rem 0 0.6rem; color: var(--coral); }

  .about-cta {
    margin-top: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--coral);
    background: var(--card);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
</style>
